<dl id="n40046b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40046b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40046b"> 46(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> humanity of <font face="wake">+</font> / = bait / devil fish snaps / invisible hook / = divinity It was held by Gregory of Nyssa, Ambrose, who uses the phrase <i>pia fraus</i>, Augustine, Leo I., and Gregory I., who expresses it in its worst form. &ldquo;The humanity of Christ was the bait; the fish, the devil, snapped at it, and was left hanging on the invisible hook, Christ&apos;s divinity&rdquo; (iii. 307).</blockquote> </dl>
